A couple of wartime sweethearts who were married for almost 72 years have been buried next to each other after dying days apart
Ronald Pearson and his wife Miriam met at an evening dance while he was serving in the RAF police and she the Auxiliary Territorial Service during the Second World War
They married in 1943 and settled in Broughton near Chester
Ronald and Miriam Pearson died last month within two days of each other
